=Baldwin Calls Snap Election

Feeling he needs to break from Bonar Law's free trade election pledge, and facing conflict within his cabinet. The Prime Minister has called a snap election to persue a more protectionist mandate under his own name. 

The King has dissolved parliament, and new elections are scheduled for next month, in December.

- @good: Great!

